SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04479402
Version: 1

HPSBGN03142 rev.1 - HP Business Service Automation Essentials running Bash
Shell, Remote Code Execution

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2014-10-17
Last Updated: 2014-10-17

Potential Security Impact: Remote code execution

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with HP Business
Service Automation Essentials . This is the Bash Shell vulnerability known as
"Shellshock" which could be exploited remotely to allow execution of code.

This vulnerability allows users that have been granted access to a shell
script to escalate privilege and execute unrestricted commands at the same
security level as the Bash script.

References:

CVE-2014-6271
CVE-2014-6277
CVE-2014-6278
CVE-2014-7169
CVE-2014-7186
CVE-2014-7187
SSRT101764

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP Business Service Automation Essentials 9.1, 9.2

